    "source_title": "Ugaritic texts (Baal Cycle)",
    "summary": "The earliest thematic origin for a divine being conquering the sea is found in older Canaanite mythology, particularly the Baal Cycle discovered in Ugarit, dating to the Late Bronze Age. These texts, which predate the destruction of Ugarit around 1200 BCE, describe a cosmic battle between the storm-god Baal and the sea-god Yam. This 'Chaoskampf' (struggle against chaos) motif is a strong literary precedent that likely influenced the biblical authors, who adapted the theme to describe Yahweh's victory over the sea.",
