  "reasoning": "While the biblical story is traditionally set in the Late Bronze Age (c. 15th-13th centuries BCE), scholarly consensus places the writing of the narrative much later. The story's core motif—a divine figure defeating a chaotic sea—has clear precedents in earlier Canaanite mythology, specifically the Baal Cycle from Ugarit (c. 13th-12th centuries BCE). The Israelite version of this theme likely existed as an oral tradition, with the first textual allusions appearing in prophetic books around the 8th century BCE. The full, canonical narrative was compiled as part of the Pentateuch around the 5th century BCE. Its subsequent translation into Greek (the Septuagint) and its inclusion in later religious texts like the New Testament and the Quran ensured its wide transmission and adaptation across major world religions.",
